cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.SC. 

The paper deals with a geometric problem of distributing runners on a circle, which suggests that it may belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of polynomials and their roots also suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The analysis of the distribution of runners and the use of asymptotic notation suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of computational statistics (cs.SC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
